She made port in Italy, Greece and Israel, where the crew was able to visit Rome's Coliseum and Vatican, Jerusalem's Old City and Wailing Wall, and Athens' Parthenon. The ship and her crew also visited the Greek islands of Crete, Rhodes, and Corfu.

'It was an incredible experience visiting these places,' said Seaman Remigio Vallin. '[It's] one thing to see these places from afar, but when you can reach out touch them; I never thought it could be this beautiful.'

